        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SCALE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Dinosaur Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">EXTINCT is your X-tile bingo:</span> At 7 letters with X=8, EXTINCT (16pts + 50 bonus = 66pts) is one of the most powerful bingos containing X. Keep E, T, I, N, C, T when you hold X.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PETRIFY combines F and Y:</span> F=4 and Y=4 together in PETRIFY (15pts) give you 8 points from just two tiles. Add P=3 and it's a strong 7-letter play worth 65 points with bingo.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FOSSIL uses the F tile reliably:</span> F=4 is often hard to play well. FOSSIL (9pts) uses it with common tiles (O, S, S, I, L) — a solid dump play that clears difficult letters.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Dinosaur words are <span class="text-white font-medium">X-tile and F-tile specialists</span>. EXTINCT delivers X=8 in a bingo, FOSSIL and PETRIFY use F=4 effectively, and EPOCH pairs P+C+H for 10 points from three tiles. When you draw X or F, think prehistoric — this vocabulary handles them naturally.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
